        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We tested <span class="accent">10 tools</span> through a legal-specific lens.</h2>
      <p>Attorneys billing $200–500/hour lose significant revenue when spending time on keyword research, content, or GBP management. Law firm SEO has unique requirements: legal directories (Avvo, FindLaw, Justia, Martindale-Hubbell) matter more than Yelp; client reviews carry outsized weight; practice area pages must target hyper-specific queries. We measured every tool against these benchmarks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 legal-specific criteria.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Same scorecard across all 10 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Legal content creation</h4>
              <p>Can it produce practice area blog posts and GBP content? "How much does a divorce cost in Texas" queries drive consultation requests.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Legal directory citations</h4>
              <p>Does it submit to Avvo, FindLaw, Justia, Martindale-Hubbell? Legal directories carry more authority for attorney rankings than generic directories.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Review management</h4>
              <p>Can it monitor and respond to Google, Avvo, and legal review sites? 84% of people trust online reviews as much as personal referrals when hiring lawyers.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Local pack rankings</h4>
              <p>Does it track Map Pack visibility for "[practice area] lawyer near me" queries? 46% of Google searches have local intent.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Billable hour ROI</h4>
              <p>How much attorney time does it save per month? At $200–500/hour, tools saving 5 hours/month equal $1,000–2,500 in recovered billing.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Content creation has the highest ROI for most law firms.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Key patterns across the evaluation.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content generates clients — tracking doesn't</h4>
              <p>Publishing 30 articles monthly targeting queries like "how much does a personal injury lawyer cost" generates more consultations than weekly rank tracking without content publication.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
