  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 SEO tools for lawyers, <span class="accent">ranked by client acquisition impact.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, one-paragraph verdict, pros, and one honest con.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · $99/MO BLOG · $49/MO LOCAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best automated blog + local SEO for law firms</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For any law firm that wants to publish consistently without taking attorneys away from billable work.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">theStacc publishes 30 blog articles monthly without attorney involvement — targeting long-tail legal queries like "how much does a personal injury lawyer cost" and "what to expect from a divorce mediation." Plus 30 GBP posts monthly. At $3.30 per article versus $150+ from freelancers, it saves 30+ billable hours monthly. On-page optimization (headers, meta descriptions, internal linking) is included.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>30 articles monthly — zero attorney time required</h4>
              <p>Content publishes automatically to your site. No brief reviews, no editing sessions, no back-and-forth with freelancers.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>$3.30 per article vs. $150+ from freelancers</h4>
              <p>At 30 articles monthly, the savings versus a freelance writer are $4,400+ per month, before accounting for attorney review time.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
