            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · FREE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Google Business Profile — Best free local listing for attorneys</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The foundation every law firm must claim and optimize before investing in any paid tool.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">GBP controls your appearance in the Map Pack for "lawyer near me" searches. It supports up to 10 practice area categories, a Q&A section for common legal questions, service area descriptions, and review collection. All free. The Q&A section alone is an underused opportunity — attorneys can post and answer common questions that appear directly in search results.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Supports up to 10 practice area categories</h4><p>List personal injury, family law, criminal defense, and more — all driving relevant Map Pack appearances.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Q&A section for common legal questions</h4><p>Attorney-posted Q&As appear directly in search results and build trust before the first click.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: 3–5 hours weekly maintenance</h4><p>Posts, responses, photos — all manual. Pair with theStacc to automate GBP posting without losing attorney time.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $39–59/MO PER LOCATION</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">BrightLocal — Best local SEO tracking suite for attorneys</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For firms that want to track Map Pack visibility by neighborhood and monitor citation consistency across legal directories.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">BrightLocal's geo-grid rank tracking shows Map Pack visibility by neighborhood — critical for firms serving specific areas of a city. It audits NAP consistency across Google, Bing, Facebook, Yelp, and Avvo. Review monitoring with alerts. GBP post scheduling (manual writing required). Competitor tracking. The most complete local tracking suite for law firms at this price.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Geo-grid shows Map Pack visibility by neighborhood</h4><p>See exactly where you're visible in the city versus where competitors dominate — down to specific blocks.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Citation auditing including Avvo</h4><p>Catches inconsistencies on legal directories that other tools miss.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: no content creation</h4><p>BrightLocal measures the ranking problem. theStacc fixes it. Use them together for a complete setup.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · FROM $299/MO · ANNUAL CONTRACTS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Birdeye — Best review management for law firms</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For firms with high client volume that need automated review collection across Google, Avvo, and 150+ review sites.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Birdeye automates review solicitation via text and email, routes positive reviews to public sites (and negative reviews to private feedback), monitors 150+ review platforms, and provides HIPAA-compliant options for relevant practices. With 84% of people trusting reviews as much as referrals when hiring lawyers, review velocity directly impacts Map Pack rankings.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Automated review solicitation — routes to Google, Avvo, Yelp</h4><p>Negative sentiment goes to private feedback; positive reviews post publicly. Smart routing increases overall star ratings.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Sentiment tracking and review analytics</h4><p>Identify recurring client concerns before they become negative public reviews.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: expensive and requires annual commitment</h4><p>Annual contracts typically required. Verify terms before signing — the cancellation terms can be complicated.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
