    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · $52/MO + LOCAL ADD-ONS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">SE Ranking — Best full SEO suite with local features for attorneys</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For law firms with a dedicated marketing person who want keyword research, rank tracking, and competitor analysis in one platform.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">SE Ranking delivers keyword research that reveals search volume, difficulty, and CPC for legal terms — useful for prioritizing which practice areas to target first. Site audit identifies technical SEO issues. Competitor analysis shows which firms rank for your target queries. Local features are add-ons at $9–23/month per location. More affordable than Semrush with similar core functionality.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Keyword research with CPC data for legal terms</h4><p>Knowing that "personal injury lawyer [city]" has $200 CPC helps prioritize which keywords to pursue through content vs. ads.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Competitor analysis shows which firms rank for target queries</h4><p>Identify which content competing firms have that you don't — and close the gap.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: local features are paid add-ons</h4><p>Local SEO features aren't included in the base price. The AI writer isn't optimized for legal accuracy and requires attorney review before publishing.</p></div></li>
